PN,31801
SC,0001
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1772482267
OL,3,CThe unremarkable winter that felt
OL,4,Canything but
OL,6,FThis winter in the UK will be chalked
OL,7,Fup relatively unremarkable - mild-ish,
OL,8,Fwet-ish and rather dull.
OL,10,FIs that how it felt to you? No, me
OL,11,Fneither! For many, it has felt
OL,12,Frelentlessly chilly, miserably wet and
OL,13,Fsoul-sappingly interminable. Here's
OL,14,Fthe true picture that has been lost in
OL,15,Fthe averaging out of one of the most
OL,16,Fpeculiar winters in recent memory.
OL,18,FHow wet was it really?
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/18
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31802
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1772482267
OL,3,CThe unremarkable winter that felt
OL,4,Canything but
OL,6,FThe Met Office conclude nine percent
OL,7,Fmore rainfall than average fell;
OL,8,F"wetter than average, but nowhere near
OL,9,Frecord-breaking territory", it said.
OL,11,FDig a little deeper and the numbers
OL,12,Fput England as the wettest nation; 35%
OL,13,Fabove the winter long term average,
OL,14,Ffollowed by Northern Ireland at 25%
OL,15,Fabove, then Wales at 14% above and,
OL,16,Fastonishingly Scotland falling 16%
OL,17,Fbelow its expected winter rainfall.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/18
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31803
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1772482267
OL,3,CThe unremarkable winter that felt
OL,4,Canything but
OL,6,FBut how can that be when Cornwall and
OL,7,FDorset have just experienced one of
OL,8,Ftheir wettest winters on record with
OL,9,Fnearly double their average rainfall,
OL,10,Fand Bodmin in Cornwall seeing an
OL,11,Fastonishing 55 consecutive days of
OL,12,Frain?!
OL,14,FClose to record-breaking rainfall too
OL,15,Ffor County Down, the Isle of Wight,
OL,16,FAngus, Kincardineshire, Hampshire and
OL,17,FAberdeen - who alone saw again,
OL,18,Fgetting on for double their expected
OL,19,Frainfall.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/18
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31804
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1772482267
OL,3,CThe unremarkable winter that felt
OL,4,Canything but
OL,6,FSubscribe free to our weekly
OL,7,Fnewsletter for exclusive and original
OL,8,Fcoverage from ITV News. Direct to your
OL,9,Finbox every Friday morning.
OL,11,FSo how can it be far from record-
OL,12,Fbreaking with these kinds of totals?
OL,14,FThe answer lies at the root of what is
OL,15,Factually so remarkable about this
OL,16,Fwinter; it's the bizarre and extremely
OL,17,Funusual distribution of rain.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/18
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31805
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1772482267
OL,3,CThe unremarkable winter that felt
OL,4,Canything but
OL,6,FOur winters usually follow a pattern
OL,7,Fof rain arriving from the west,
OL,8,Fcrossing the UK and then heading away
OL,9,Ffrom us across the North Sea.
OL,11,FBeing exposed to these rain-bearing
OL,12,FAtlantic frontal systems first means
OL,13,Fthat western parts usually bear the
OL,14,Fbrunt of the short, sharp bursts of
OL,15,Fheavy rain, less so across more
OL,16,Fcentral and eastern areas and the
OL,17,Fsouth coast. So high rainfall amounts
OL,18,Fin these areas? That would be normal
OL,19,Fand average for them.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/18
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31806
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1772482267
OL,3,CThe unremarkable winter that felt
OL,4,Canything but
OL,6,FBut look at this map and notice the
OL,7,Fdarkest blues where the heaviest of
OL,8,Frain has fallen; eastern Scotland,
OL,9,Feastern parts of Northern Ireland.
OL,10,Ftraditionally sheltered parts of both
OL,11,Fthe south coast and central England.
OL,12,FAnd now look at western Scotland! It's
OL,13,Fbrown (and dry!) where it should be
OL,14,Fblue (and wet!).
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/18
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31807
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1772482267
OL,3,CThe unremarkable winter that felt
OL,4,Canything but
OL,6,FBasic mathematics dictates that to get
OL,7,Fthe average, (the total rain divided
OL,8,Facross the number of weather
OL,9,Fstations), the very dry goes a long
OL,10,Fway to balance out the very wet
OL,11,Fleaving us with a figure that is far
OL,12,Fand away from someone's lived
OL,13,Fexperience of the past three months!
OL,15,FIs the same true for sunshine?
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/18
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31808
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1772482267
OL,3,CThe unremarkable winter that felt
OL,4,Canything but
OL,6,FYes! Again the distribution of
OL,7,Fsunshine is highly irregular. 25 days
OL,8,Fwithout any recordable sunshine at all
OL,9,Fin Aberdeen for example, which would
OL,10,Fusually be far brighter than its more
OL,11,Fwesterly cities is far from usual.
OL,13,FWhat about temperatures? It certainly
OL,14,Fdidn't feel mild and yet the data
OL,15,Fshows that it was!
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/18
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31809
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1772482267
OL,3,CThe unremarkable winter that felt
OL,4,Canything but
OL,6,FHere's another story that is lost in
OL,7,Fthe averaging out. Yes it felt chilly
OL,8,Fby day, in large part down to the lack
OL,9,Fof sunshine - but how many times did
OL,10,Fyou have to scrape your car in the
OL,11,Fmorning? For many of us, the answer is
OL,12,F'not many'. Yes there were some spells
OL,13,Fof snow for some - but this fell in
OL,14,Fareas that we would usually expect it
OL,15,F- the high ground in the north.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/18
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31810
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1772482267
OL,3,CThe unremarkable winter that felt
OL,4,Canything but
OL,6,FFurther south, to have only a handful
OL,7,Fof frosty nights and icy mornings -
OL,8,Fthat's a sign that it was our nights
OL,9,Fthat were mild - and it's that
OL,10,Ftemperature that pulls up the overall
OL,11,Fwinter average.
OL,13,FSo what was the reason that things
OL,14,Fwere so different this year?
OL,16,FI mentioned above that our usual
OL,17,Fpattern is rain-bearing Atlantic
OL,18,Ffrontal systems bringing in rain from
OL,19,Fthe west and then clearing east,
OL,20,Fusually easing and fragmenting as it
OL,21,Fcleared away.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/18
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31811
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1772482267
OL,3,CThe unremarkable winter that felt
OL,4,Canything but
OL,6,FThis year, however, a huge area of
OL,7,Fhigh pressure has sat out to the east
OL,8,Fof us effectively blocking the
OL,9,Fclearance of those rain-bearing
OL,10,Ffronts. Essentially, with systems
OL,11,Fstalling over the UK, rain has been
OL,12,Ffast to arrive and slow to leave.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G11/18
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31812
SC,0012
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1772482267
OL,3,CThe unremarkable winter that felt
OL,4,Canything but
OL,6,FWe've also had to contend with a
OL,7,F'powered up jet stream' which acts as
OL,8,Fa conveyor belt for frontal systems.
OL,9,FThis fast-moving current of air in the
OL,10,Fupper atmosphere has been supercharged
OL,11,Fover the last few months thanks to a
OL,12,Fmuch starker than usual temperature
OL,13,Fcontrast across the USA as a result of
OL,14,Fsome exceptional winter snow storms.
OL,16,FSo the rain that has arrived across
OL,17,Fthe UK has been both heavier and
OL,18,Fslower to clear.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G12/18
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31813
SC,0013
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1772482267
OL,3,CThe unremarkable winter that felt
OL,4,Canything but
OL,6,FAnd there's one more crucial
OL,7,Fdifference this year. That jet stream
OL,8,Fthat has been firing rain bearing
OL,9,FAtlantic systems at us? It's been what
OL,10,Fforecasters term 'south-shifted' -
OL,11,Fthose fronts, usually on course for
OL,12,Fwestern areas, have instead fed in on
OL,13,Fa more south/southeasterly wind.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G13/18
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31814
SC,0014
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1772482267
OL,3,CThe unremarkable winter that felt
OL,4,Canything but
OL,6,FAnd, now, if you look at those maps
OL,7,Fagain and imagine cloud bearing, rain
OL,8,Fbearing frontal systems coming in from
OL,9,Fthe south/southeast rather than the
OL,10,Fwest, it starts to make sense.
OL,11,FRemember too that a south/
OL,12,Fsoutheasterly airflow is also less
OL,13,Fcold than one from the north (the
OL,14,FArctic) and all those frost free
OL,15,Fnights start to make sense too.
OL,17,FIf so much is lost in averaging,
OL,18,Fwhat's the point?
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G14/18
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31815
SC,0015
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1772482267
OL,3,CThe unremarkable winter that felt
OL,4,Canything but
OL,6,FThe Met Office averages data to show
OL,7,Fthe overall climate trend across the
OL,8,FUK, allowing scientists to compare
OL,9,Fseasons and years consistently. Think
OL,10,Fof it like a school report; if the
OL,11,Fwhole class averages 70%, it doesn't
OL,12,Fmean every student scored 70% ` some
OL,13,Fgot 90%, some 50% but it gives a
OL,14,Fgeneral overview of progress or
OL,15,Fdecline. The average highlights big-
OL,16,Fpicture patterns, tracks long term
OL,17,Ftrends and allows a like-for-like
OL,18,Fcomparable from one year to another.
OL,19,FWhat the national figures can't tell
OL,20,Fhowever is the lived experience of a
OL,21,Fparticular area.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G15/18
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31816
SC,0016
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1772482267
OL,3,CThe unremarkable winter that felt
OL,4,Canything but
OL,6,FSo how much was this winter down to
OL,7,Fclimate change?
OL,9,FThe Met Office have said that 'while
OL,10,Fthis winter's weather has been heavily
OL,11,Finfluenced by natural variability and
OL,12,Fatmospheric patterns, climate change
OL,13,Fprovides important context.'
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G16/18
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31817
SC,0017
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1772482267
OL,3,CThe unremarkable winter that felt
OL,4,Canything but
OL,6,FA warmer atmosphere holds more water;
OL,7,Fessentially when it rains, it now
OL,8,Frains more. This winter might be
OL,9,Fexplained by natural variability in
OL,10,Fweather patterns - but it unfolded in
OL,11,Fa climate that is now warmer than in
OL,12,Fthe past. There is no doubt that
OL,13,Ffuture UK winters are expected to
OL,14,Ffeature more days with significant
OL,15,Frainfall making wet winters
OL,16,Fincreasingly common in the long term.
OL,18,FFor now though, it's officially spring
OL,19,Fat last! And, come rain or shine,
OL,20,Fthat's surely something to smile about!
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G17/18
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
